{
  "stem": "11133.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we stood there for a long time, and-- you know, if the count did not jive, you had to wait until it jived before they would excuse us to go to our work.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "From the time-- from the time we started going from the ghetto to the-- to the factory, we always walked in fives.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that sort of became-- after the war, it was very difficult to walk alone.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] You always looked on either side of you to see whether you had your teammates with you, or your people from your five.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But for me, that was very good, because I was a child.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And though I was tall, by being able to walk amongst other five, I was not as prominent.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that's-- you know-- that was a security measure for me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the time, yes, there were quite a few children still, you know, in Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As long as it was a labor camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the one day, they had a selection in Plaszow, and they took a lot of the children away.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And some of the children hid themselves in the latrines.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, that's how they survived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember, we smuggled a couple children out in our fives, you know, in sacks between us, out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then, once the camp became a concentration camp, we no longer could go out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so Madritsch established his factory in the camp, in some barracks, away from the living quarters.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At that point, of course, in Plaszow already, one other thing that happened when the ghetto closed is that my father, of course, then became part of the men's section, and my mother and I became part of the women's section.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we weren't reunited again until after the war, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
